<document><title><tag>tabular</tag> component</title>

<section><title>Associated Attributes</title>
<ul>
  <li><attr>width</attr>  <em>(_componentSize)</em></li>
  <li><attr>height</attr>  <em>(_componentSize)</em></li>
  <li><attr>halign</attr>  <em>(text)</em></li>
  <li><attr>valign</attr>  <em>(text)</em></li>
  <li><attr>top</attr>  <em>(text)</em></li>
  <li><attr>left</attr>  <em>(text)</em></li>
  <li><attr>bottom</attr>  <em>(text)</em></li>
  <li><attr>right</attr>  <em>(text)</em></li>
</ul>

</section>


<section><title>Description</title>
<!--use <ref> on all component names (other than the one indexed from this file) in this section only-->
  <p>The <tag>tablular</tag><idx><tag>tablular</tag></idx> component contains the data and style specifications for a <tag><ref>table</ref></tag>. Nested inside a <tag>tabular</tag> component are the <tag><ref>row</ref></tag>, <tag><ref>cell</ref></tag>, and if used, the <tag><ref>column</ref></tag> components.  See examples below.</p>
</section> 

  
<section><title>Usage Examples</title>

<subsection><title>Example 1: <tag>tabular</tag> without attributes </title>
<p>In the code below, the <tag>tabular</tag> component is used in the standard manner, nested inside a <tag>table</tag> component and without any attributes specified.</p>  

<example boxed="true"><title>Sample DoenetML code (Example 1)</title>
<pre>
  
&lt;table&gt;&lt;title&gt;Fake Weather Statistics&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;tabular&gt;
    &lt;row header&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;Time&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;Mon&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;Tue&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;Wed&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
          
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🌧&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;❄️&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;☀️&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
        
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;AM&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;rain&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;snow&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;sunny&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
          
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;50&lt;m&gt;^{\circ}&lt;/m&gt;&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;15&lt;m&gt;^{\circ}&lt;/m&gt;&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;-10&lt;m&gt;^{\circ}&lt;/m&gt;&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
  &lt;/tabular&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</pre>
  </example>
</subsection>
  
