<subsection><title>Example2: <tag>tabular</tag> with border attributes </title>
<p>In the code below, the attributes <attr>top</attr>, <attr>bottom</attr>, <attr>left</attr>, and <attr>right</attr> are used to specify the overall surrounding border for the <tag>table</tag> within the <tag>tabular</tag> component.  Valid values for this attribute are <c>"none", "major", "medium"</c> and <c>"minor"</c>.  The default value for all border linetype attributes is <c>"none"</c>.</p>

<example boxed="true"><title>Sample DoenetML code (Example 2)</title>
<pre>
&lt;table suppressTableNameInTitle="true" number="false"&gt;&lt;title&gt;**This table has no automatic Title**&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;tabular top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium"&gt;
    &lt;row bottom="minor"&gt;
      &lt;cell right="minor"&gt;Data 1&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell right="minor"&gt;Data 2&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;Data 3&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
          
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell right="minor"&gt;A&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell right="minor"&gt;B&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;C&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;/row&gt;
    &lt;/tabular&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</pre>
  </example>
</subsection>
 
<!--*******************************************************-->
 
<example><title>What Doenet Renders (Example 2)</title>


    <table suppressTableNameInTitle="true" number="false"><title>**This table has no automatic Title**</title>
        <tabular top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
          <row bottom="minor">
            <cell right="minor">Data 1</cell>
            <cell right="minor">Data 2</cell>
