<subsection><title>Example 3: <tag>tabular</tag> with alignment attributes</title>
<p>In the code below, the <attr>width</attr>, <attr>height</attr>, <attr>valign</attr> and <attr>halign</attr> attributes are used with the <tag>tabular</tag> component.  Valid values for the <attr>valign</attr> attribute are: <c>"top", "middle"</c> and <c>"right"</c> and the default value is <c>"middle"</c>. Valid values for the <attr>halign</attr> attribute are: <c>"left", "center", "justify",</c> and <c>"right"</c> and the default value is <c>"left"</c>.  If an attribute is specified in both a parent and a child component, the styling specified by the child component governs.</p>

<example boxed="true"><title>Sample DoenetML code (Example 3)</title>
  
<pre>
&lt;table&gt;&lt;title&gt;Nonsense emoji shuffle&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;tabular width="500" height="300" bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium"
    halign="left" valign="bottom"&gt;
    &lt;row halign="center"&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔴&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔵&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟢&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
    
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟢&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟣&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔵&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
    
    &lt;row valign="top"&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟠&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔴&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟣&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
  &lt;/tabular&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</pre>
  </example>
</subsection>

<!--*******************************************************-->

